meson-mode.el: fix "undeclared function evil-local-set-key" warning

This fixes a warning:

    In end of data:
    meson-mode.el:958:12: Warning: the function ‘evil-local-set-key’ is not known to be defined.

We pass `nil` as the filename because it's up to Evil project to
organize sources and it would not be really good to hardcode their
layout here.

commit.message:
utils.el: fix "no lexical binding" warning

Upstream Emacs has enabled warnings for `.el` files with no
lexical-binding directive, so this file triggers a:

    In toplevel form:
    lsp.el:1:1: Warning: file has no ‘lexical-binding’ directive on its first line

Fix that.

utils.el: replace `add-to-list` with `push`

`add-to-list` can't be used with lexical binding, which is probably
why its documentation discourages the use. So replace this with `push`

Fixes compilation error:

    In refman2func-doc:
    utils.el:29:12: Error: ‘add-to-list’ can’t use lexical var ‘functions’; use ‘push’ or ‘cl-pushnew’

commit.message: README.md: Re-generate

Fix indentation of list arguments

References #21

Don't use tabs for indentation

This is recommended in the Meson Style
Guide (https://mesonbuild.com/Style-guide.html).
Indent dictionaries the same way as arrays

Use display-buffer instead of switch-to-buffer to show documentation

Using switch-to-buffer to show the manual is not ideal because it
always shows the Meson manual in the currently selected window. If the
manual is already shown in another window, the user ends up with two
windows showing the manual. This commit prevents this by using
display-buffer with appropriate actions so that the manual is shown in
the same window where it was before. Only if the manual is not
visible, it opens in the selected window.

Another advantage of display-buffer is that it is user-configurable.
To that end, this commits introduces meson-doc-display-buffer-action,
which can be customized if someone prefers to select windows for
displaying the manual differently.

meson-lookup-doc: Don't preserve window pos

This fixes the issue that you can only lookup once in the manual (when
the buffer is not yet assigned with an existing window)
